
== CONFIG ==

This directory contains all settings and customisation files for ATC-pie. Its
contents is listed below, with a description for each sub-directory or file.



*** DIRECTORIES ***

Each directory below contains a "Notice" file of its own with more information
about its purpose and contents.

 - CONFIG/acft: aircraft data base and FlightGear model conversions
 - CONFIG/ad:   airfield source data (custom/imported "apt.dat" files)
 - CONFIG/bg:   background images for radars and loose strip bays
 - CONFIG/elev: ground elevation maps (for solo and teaching sessions)
 - CONFIG/loc:  location-specific settings reloaded between sessions
 - CONFIG/nav:  navigation and routing data
 - CONFIG/phon: pronunciation of airline callsigns and navpoint names



*** FILES ***

Any of the files below can be deleted to restore defaults.


1. "settings.conf"
2. "text-radio-messages.conf"

These files store the settings that are reloaded between sessions. The text
radio message presets are saved separately for convenience.

Both files are loaded when a location is open, and saved (written over) when its
window is closed. You can therefore edit them between sessions, but should use
the application interface while a session is running not to lose your changes.
All saved settings can be changed from the application interface.


3. "CTR-positions.conf"

This file contains the radar centre positions for the CTR locations proposed in
the launcher.

It is loaded on program start-up, and saved (written over) on exit. You can
therefore edit it between runs, but should not do so while the program is
running not to lose your changes.


4. "colours.conf"

You may customise display colours by editing this file, generated on start-up if
not already present. It can be edited and reloaded from the "System" menu while
the program is running.

Colours are specified with SVG colour keyword names like "white" or RGB hex
strings of the form "RRGGBB". Line comments, starting with '#', are allowed.


5. "main-stylesheet.qss"

If present at start-up, this Qt stylesheet will be applied to the main window
and its child dialogs. It can be edited and reloaded from the "System" menu
while the program is running.

For a specification of the Qt stylesheet syntax: doc.qt.io/qt-5/stylesheet.html


6. "dock-layout.bin"

This binary file is created by ATC-pie when saving the window and dock geometry
from the "View" menu. It is not editable.

